latestIgtvVideos.title: Print On Print
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
@amazonfashionin got me to step out of my fashion comfort zone and made me experiment with print on print because I’ve always thought solids were more my vibe. They gave me the theme “Print clash” (which I was a little nervous about) and asked me to order and style some clothes from the website directly - just like any shopper would. I was surprised at how cool some of the clothes were. Here are the things I bought and didn’t return :

Checked pants 
Polka dot shirt 
Striped shirt 
Printed Dress 
All the accessories + the flats 

We shot the entire thing in our new office by on an iPhone!  What do you guys think?

Some perfectly timed photos my wonderful hair artist took on my phone before I left for the @sabyasachiofficial show in January, outside the hotel I was staying at. With half the year gone, this still remains a look I enjoyed putting together the most. Sabyasachi has a unique way of making you show up as your most creative self, and of course the drama and hype around the show is forever etched in my memory. I’m wearing an @arokaofficial slip dress with the chiffon dupatta it comes with, layered with two @sabyasachiofficial belts. The jewllery is all antique (mostly my grandmum’s) mixed and matched. The emerald necklace I wore for one of my wedding functions. Another reminder that jewellery is meant to be worn as often as possible ;)
